50|$|Oregon was 6.5% {{larger and}} 4 feet wider than Alaska, {{but the same}} length to reduce her ratio of length to beam and address the serious {{vibration}} problem experienced by Arizona and Alaska. Consideration was given to building Oregon of steel after the fisaco of the City of Rome, but the new metal was still expensive and hard to obtain. Oregon was the last iron record breaker. She had nine <b>transverse</b> <b>watertight</b> <b>bulkheads,</b> five iron decks, and a strong turtle-back deck forward and aft as a protection from the heavy seas.|$|R
