5000|$|Pluton was 152.5 m long overall. She had {{a beam of}} 15.5 m and a {{draft of}} 5.2 m. Her {{longitudinally}} framed hull was subdivided by 15 <b>transverse</b> <b>watertight</b> <b>bulkheads.</b> Duralumin was extensively used in the superstructure to save weight, but this resulted in corrosion problems and strength issues. She was fitted with a single counterbalanced rudder powered by an electric motor that was too weak for the job. Her turning circle was 875 m with 25° of rudder at 27 kn, larger {{than that of the}} 8000 t light cruiser [...] which was 30 m longer. She was totally unarmored and relied upon her watertight subdivision for survival.|$|R
